.TH MUXM 1 "2026-02-23" "MuxMaster v0.11.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
muxm \- video encoder/muxer with Dolby Vision, HDR10, HLG, and SDR support
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B muxm
[\fIoptions\fR] \fIsource\fR [\fItarget\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
MuxMaster (\fBmuxm\fR) converts and muxes video for playback on Apple TV, Plex,
and a wide range of devices. It handles Dolby Vision (extract/convert/inject),
HDR/HLG/SDR color matching, smart audio selection and transcoding, subtitle
selection with optional PGS\(->SRT OCR, and multi-container output (MP4, MKV,
M4V, MOV).
.PP
The recommended way to use \fBmuxm\fR is with \fB\-\-profile\fR, which configures
dozens of settings for a specific use case in a single flag. Every setting a
profile changes can be individually overridden with CLI flags.
.SH PROFILES
Profiles are named presets that configure \fBmuxm\fR for a target workflow.
.TP
.B dv\-archival
Dolby Vision archival. Copies video without re-encoding, passes lossless audio
through, keeps all subtitles and chapters, and generates a JSON report. Skips
processing entirely if the source already matches. Container: MKV.
.TP
.B hdr10\-hq
High quality HDR10. Strips Dolby Vision layers and re-encodes to clean HDR10
HEVC at CRF 17. Preserves lossless audio (TrueHD, DTS-HD MA, FLAC) and adds a
stereo fallback track. Container: MKV.
.TP
.B atv\-directplay\-hq
Apple TV Direct Play. Targets true Direct Play on Apple TV 4K via Plex: MP4
container, HEVC Main10 with DV Profile 8.1 when possible, E-AC-3 surround with
AAC stereo fallback, and forced subtitle burn-in. Copies compliant video
without re-encoding. Skips processing if source is already ATV-compliant.
.TP
.B universal
Universal compatibility. Plays on everything: old Rokus, mobile devices, web
browsers, non-HDR TVs. Tone-maps HDR to SDR, encodes to H.264, forces AAC
stereo audio, burns forced subtitles, exports others as external SRT, and
strips chapters and non-essential metadata. Container: MP4.
.PP
Profiles can also be set as a default in any \fB.muxmrc\fR config file:
.PP
.RS
PROFILE_NAME="atv\-directplay\-hq"
.RE
.PP
CLI \fB\-\-profile\fR always overrides a config-file PROFILE_NAME.
.SH CORE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show usage and exit.
.TP
.BR \-V ", " \-\-version
Show version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-\-install\-dependencies
Check for all required and optional tools, install missing ones via Homebrew
and pipx, verify environment settings (Tesseract language data, TESSDATA_PREFIX),
and exit. Does not encode anything.
.TP
.BR \-\-profile " " \fINAME\fR
Apply a named format profile (\fBdv\-archival\fR, \fBhdr10\-hq\fR,
\fBatv\-directplay\-hq\fR, \fBuniversal\fR). CLI flags given after \-\-profile
override the profile's defaults.
.TP
.BR \-\-print\-effective\-config
Show the fully resolved configuration after merging config files, profile, and
CLI flags, then exit. Useful for verifying what a profile actually sets.
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Plan steps and create stub artifacts without encoding or muxing.
.TP
.BR \-\-checksum
Write a SHA-256 checksum file alongside the output.
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-keep\-temp
Keep the temporary working directory on failure (useful for inspecting
per-stage error logs like \fIencode.err\fR, \fIaudio_primary.err\fR,
\fImux.err\fR).
.TP
.BR \-K ", " \-\-keep\-temp\-always
Keep the temporary working directory even on success.
.TP
.BR \-\-skip\-if\-ideal
Skip processing entirely if the source already matches the target profile.
Enabled by default in \fBdv\-archival\fR and \fBatv\-directplay\-hq\fR profiles.
.TP
.BR \-\-report\-json
Generate a machine-readable JSON report alongside the output.
.SH VIDEO OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-crf " " \fIN\fR
x265/x264 quality CRF value (lower = higher quality). Typical range: 17\(en22.
Default: 18.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-preset " " \fINAME\fR
x265/x264 encoder preset: ultrafast, superfast, veryfast, faster, fast, medium,
slow, slower, veryslow, placebo. Default: slower.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-level " " \fIN\fR
HEVC level-idc (e.g., 4.1, 5.0, 5.1). When set, conservative VBV rate
control is applied automatically. Default: encoder decides.
.TP
.BR \-\-x265\-params " " \fISTR\fR
Override the base x265 parameter string. Advanced.
.TP
.BR \-\-video\-codec " " libx265|libx264
Video encoder. Default: libx265. Set to libx264 by the \fBuniversal\fR profile.
.TP
.BR \-\-video\-copy\-if\-compliant
Copy (stream-copy) the video track if the source already matches the target
codec and profile, skipping re-encoding. Enabled by \fBdv\-archival\fR and
\fBatv\-directplay\-hq\fR profiles.
.TP
.BR \-\-tonemap
Tone-map HDR/HLG content to SDR using a zscale+hable filter chain. Enabled by
the \fBuniversal\fR profile.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-dv
Disable Dolby Vision RPU extraction and injection entirely.
.TP
.BR \-\-allow\-dv\-fallback ", " \-\-no\-allow\-dv\-fallback
Control whether DV handling failures fall back gracefully to non-DV output
(default: allow fallback) or hard-fail the pipeline.
.TP
.BR \-\-dv\-convert\-p81 ", " \-\-no\-dv\-convert\-p81
Control whether non-P8.1 DV sources are converted to Profile 8.1 when DV
handling fails. Default: enabled.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-conservative\-vbv
Disable automatic VBV rate control guardrails when a level is set.
.TP
.BR \-\-threads " " \fIN\fR
Set ffmpeg thread count. Default: ffmpeg chooses automatically.
.SH AUDIO OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-audio\-track " " \fIN\fR
Force selection of a specific audio stream by index (0-based, relative to
audio streams only). Bypasses the automatic scoring/selection logic.
.TP
.BR \-\-audio\-lang\-pref " " \fILIST\fR
Preferred audio languages, comma-separated (e.g., eng,spa). Default: eng.
.TP
.BR \-\-stereo\-fallback ", " \-\-no\-stereo\-fallback
Enable or disable automatic creation of a stereo AAC track when the primary
audio has more than 2 channels. Default: enabled.
.TP
.BR \-\-stereo\-bitrate " " \fIRATE\fR
Bitrate for the stereo fallback track (e.g., 192k, 256k). Default: 192k.
.TP
.BR \-\-audio\-force\-codec " " \fICODEC\fR
Force all audio output to a specific codec (e.g., aac). Used by the
\fBuniversal\fR profile.
.TP
.BR \-\-audio\-lossless\-passthrough
Allow lossless audio codecs (TrueHD, DTS-HD MA, FLAC) to stream-copy through
without transcoding. Enabled by \fBdv\-archival\fR and \fBhdr10\-hq\fR profiles.
.SH SUBTITLE OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-subtitles
Exclude all subtitles from the output.
.TP
.BR \-\-sub\-lang\-pref " " \fILIST\fR
Preferred subtitle languages, comma-separated (e.g., eng,spa). Default: eng.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-sub\-sdh
Exclude SDH/HI subtitle tracks.
.TP
.BR \-\-sub\-burn\-forced
Burn forced subtitles into the video stream for guaranteed display on all
players. Enabled by \fBatv\-directplay\-hq\fR and \fBuniversal\fR profiles.
.TP
.BR \-\-sub\-export\-external
Export non-burned subtitles as external .srt files alongside the output.
Enabled by the \fBuniversal\fR profile.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-ocr
Disable PGS-to-SRT OCR. PGS bitmap subtitles will be dropped from MP4 output
(MP4 cannot carry PGS).
.TP
.BR \-\-ocr\-tool " " \fITOOL\fR
OCR tool for PGS subtitle conversion. Default: sub2srt.
.TP
.BR \-\-ocr\-lang " " \fILANG\fR
OCR language. Default: eng.
.SH OUTPUT OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-output\-ext " " mp4|m4v|mov|mkv
Output container format. Default: mp4. Profiles may change this (e.g.,
\fBdv\-archival\fR and \fBhdr10\-hq\fR use mkv).
.TP
.BR \-\-keep\-chapters ", " \-\-no\-keep\-chapters
Keep or strip chapter markers. Default: keep. The \fBuniversal\fR profile
strips chapters.
.TP
.BR \-\-strip\-metadata
Strip non-essential metadata from the output. Enabled by the \fBuniversal\fR
profile.
.SH QUICK TEST OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-skip\-video
Skip the video pipeline (cannot produce a valid final output; use for testing
audio/subtitle logic only).
.TP
.BR \-\-skip\-audio
Skip the audio pipeline entirely.
.TP
.BR \-\-skip\-subs
Skip the subtitle pipeline entirely.
.SH FFMPEG TUNING OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-ffmpeg\-loglevel " " \fILEVEL\fR
Set ffmpeg log verbosity (e.g., error, warning, info). Default: error.
.TP
.BR \-\-ffprobe\-loglevel " " \fILEVEL\fR
Set ffprobe log verbosity. Default: error.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-hide\-banner
Show the ffmpeg version banner.
.TP
.BR \-\-no\-overwrite
Do not overwrite existing temp files (ffmpeg \-n behavior).
.SH CONFIGURATION
\fBmuxm\fR reads configuration from multiple levels, applied in this order
(lowest to highest precedence):
.PP
.RS
.nf
Hardcoded defaults
  \(-> /etc/.muxmrc          (system-wide)
    \(-> ~/.muxmrc            (user defaults)
      \(-> ./.muxmrc          (project-specific)
        \(-> --profile <n>    (format profile)
          \(-> CLI flags      (highest \(em always wins)
.fi
.RE
.PP
Config files are sourced as shell scripts. Any variable from Section 4 of the
script can be set in a config file. CLI flags always take final precedence.
.PP
\fBConflict warnings:\fR \fBmuxm\fR detects contradictory flag + profile
combinations (e.g., \fB\-\-profile dv\-archival \-\-no\-dv\fR) and prints
warnings. Warnings never block execution \(em the user's CLI flags always win.
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 10
Missing required dependency (ffmpeg, ffprobe, jq).
.TP
.B 11
Invalid input: bad CLI flag, unknown option, missing or unreadable source file,
invalid output path, too many arguments, or source and output are the same file.
.TP
.B 12
Source file problem: corrupt file, no video streams found, or ffprobe returned
invalid JSON.
.TP
.B 40
Video pipeline failure: base encode failed, DV RPU extraction failed (with
fallback disabled).
.TP
.B 41
Mux or output failure: final mux failed, DV RPU injection failed, or output
file is empty or corrupt.
.TP
.B 42
Pipeline logic error: no encoded video stream available for muxing,
\fB\-\-skip\-video\fR used in a context that requires video output.
.TP
.B 43
Audio pipeline failure: audio copy or transcode failed.
.TP
.B 130
Interrupted by user (SIGINT / Ctrl+C).
.TP
.B 143
Terminated by signal (SIGTERM).
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Basic encode with defaults
.nf
muxm Movie.mkv output.mp4
muxm --crf 20 -p slow Movie.mkv output.mp4
.fi
.SS Using profiles (recommended)
.nf
# Apple TV Direct Play \(em one flag does it all
muxm --profile atv-directplay-hq Movie.mkv

# Archival \(em copy video, keep lossless audio, generate report
muxm --profile dv-archival Movie.mkv

# Universal compatibility \(em H.264 SDR, AAC stereo
muxm --profile universal Movie.mkv

# HDR10 high quality with custom CRF
muxm --profile hdr10-hq --crf 20 Movie.mkv
.fi
.SS Overriding profile defaults
.nf
# Use hdr10-hq but with a different CRF and no stereo fallback
muxm --profile hdr10-hq --crf 20 --no-stereo-fallback Movie.mkv

# Use universal but keep chapters
muxm --profile universal --keep-chapters Movie.mkv

# Use atv-directplay-hq but output to MKV (warns about compatibility)
muxm --profile atv-directplay-hq --output-ext mkv Movie.mkv
.fi
.SS Inspecting and debugging
.nf
# See what a profile actually sets
muxm --profile atv-directplay-hq --print-effective-config

# Dry run to preview the pipeline
muxm --profile universal --dry-run Movie.mkv

# Keep temp files for post-mortem inspection
muxm --keep-temp --profile hdr10-hq Movie.mkv
.fi
.SS Audio and subtitle control
.nf
# Prefer Spanish audio and English subtitles
muxm --audio-lang-pref spa,eng --sub-lang-pref eng Movie.mkv

# Force a specific audio track (0-based audio index)
muxm --audio-track 2 Movie.mkv

# Disable OCR for PGS subtitles
muxm --no-ocr Movie.mkv
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DEBUG
Set to \fB1\fR to enable bash trace output (set \-x) for low-level debugging.
.TP
.B TESSDATA_PREFIX
Path to Tesseract language data directory. Required if using pgsrip for PGS
subtitle OCR. Typically set to the Homebrew tessdata path.
.SH FILES
.TP
\fI/etc/.muxmrc\fR
System-wide configuration.
.TP
\fI~/.muxmrc\fR
User-level configuration.
.TP
\fI./.muxmrc\fR
Project-specific configuration (current working directory).
.PP
Config files are sourced as bash and may set any \fBmuxm\fR variable. CLI flags
always override config file values.
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
Required:
ffmpeg, ffprobe, jq
.TP
Recommended (Dolby Vision):
dovi_tool, mp4box (GPAC)
.TP
Optional (PGS subtitle OCR):
sub2srt or pgsrip, tesseract
.PP
Run \fBmuxm \-\-install\-dependencies\fR to check and install all of the above
via Homebrew and pipx.
